dback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 30, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kla1665702720804.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kla1665702720804.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kla1665702720804.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kla1665702720804\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">$HANKAKU_FONT1\n  </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Apply single-byte storage to FONT1 for the HANKAKU character set.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"kla1665702720804__topic_d140612e1_d140613e1_d140614e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kla1665702720804__p_d140615e1_d140616e1_d140617e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$HANKAKU_FONT1</span> {<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>} <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kla1665702720804__section_ryy_ttx_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d779690e69\">Defaults</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"kla1665702720804__table_d17120e1_d17121e1_d17122e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Assignment file:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">client assignment files</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Section:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">[SETTINGS]</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Default value:</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">0</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kla1665702720804__section_lyc_5tx_bwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d779690e115\"> escription</h2>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"kla1665702720804__note_tfp_wtx_bwb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$HANKAKU_FONT1</span> setting is\n        provided for compatibility with earlier Uniface versions. It should be used only on a\n        Japanese system.</div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kla1665702720804__p_d140624e1_d140625e1_d140626e1\">When set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">TRUE</code>, Hankaku Katakana\n        characters and ASCII can be entered when the field syntax definition MUL (Unicode range\n        00-FF) is used. The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$EXTENDED_SYNTAX</span> setting is ignored.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kla1665702720804__p_d140627e1_d140628e1_d140629e1\">There are two types of Hankaku—Hankaku Katakana (<a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://www.fileformat.info/info/unicode/char/30a1/index.htm\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.fileformat.info/info/unicode/char/30a1/index.htm</a>) containing one-byte characters, and Zenkaku Katakana (<a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://www.fileformat.info/info/unicode/char/30a2/index.htm\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.fileformat.info/info/unicode/char/30a2/index.htm</a>) containing double-byte characters.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kla1665702720804__p_d140630e1_d140631e1_d140632e1\">When <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$HANKAKU_FONT1</span> is set to\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>, all Hankaku Katakana characters in the region FF61-FF9F are mapped to\n        Font 1, that is, to extended ASCII. The setting has no effect on Zenkaku Katakana double\n        byte characters.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kla1665702720804__p_d140633e1_d140634e1_d140635e1\">When the field syntax is MUL, only characters from\n        Font 0 and Font 1 can be entered. However, some string fields may require single-byte\n        Hankaku characters as input. With MUL in the field syntax definition and\n          <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$HANKAKU_FONT1</span> set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>, ASCII and half-width\n        characters from region FF61-FF9F can be entered, nothing else.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xtc1665702555471.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$EXTENDED_SYNTAX</a><p>Specify which characters are allowed as extended characters (~&amp; or ~@) in the field syntax definition.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529253\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529253\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$HANKAKU_FONT1 Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 30, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 $HANKAKU_FONT1 Apply single-byte storage to FONT1 for the HANKAKU character set. $HANKAKU_FONT1 { = } 1 | 0 Defaults Assignment file: client assignment files Section: [SETTINGS] Default value: 0 escription Note: The $HANKAKU_FONT1 setting is provided for compatibility with earlier Uniface versions. It should be used only on a Japanese system. When set to TRUE , Hankaku Katakana characters and ASCII can be entered when the field syntax definition MUL (Unicode range 00-FF) is used. The $EXTENDED_SYNTAX setting is ignored. There are two types of Hankaku—Hankaku Katakana ( https://www.fileformat.info/info/unicode/char/30a1/index.htm ) containing one-byte characters, and Zenkaku Katakana ( https://www.fileformat.info/info/unicode/char/30a2/index.htm ) containing double-byte characters. When $HANKAKU_FONT1 is set to 1 , all Hankaku Katakana characters in the region FF61-FF9F are mapped to Font 1, that is, to extended ASCII. The setting has no effect on Zenkaku Katakana double byte characters. When the field syntax is MUL, only characters from Font 0 and Font 1 can be entered. However, some string fields may require single-byte Hankaku characters as input. With MUL in the field syntax definition and $HANKAKU_FONT1 set to 1 , ASCII and half-width characters from region FF61-FF9F can be entered, nothing else. Related Links $EXTENDED_SYNTAX Specify which characters are allowed as extended characters (~& or ~@) in the field syntax definition. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}